tate of Kentucky. That we have often heard said Aaron Chambers call his (Rea) Chambers, wife, and always treated and respected her in such relation. That they were considered as man and wife by all their neighbors and acquaintances, and considered respectable in the community in which they lived. That there are now living men of their said Aaron and Rea Chambers under the age of sixteen years. And that she has been a widow since the death of above named soldier (Aaron Chambers) dec'd. That we have 30 acres in the Valley H. C. Hinkle, Jr. W. D. Chambers Clerk of the County of Henderson Sworn to and subscribed before me, this Twenty-ninth day of September, in the year 1867, and I hereby certify that the affiants are respectable and credible persons and make no match; that I believe their names are correct and worthy of full faith and credit, and that I have no interest in this matter. I further certify that the foregoing affidavits were read over, fully explained to, and understood by the affiants before the signing and foregoing request. H. C. Hinkle N. D. H. Co. ADDITIONAL EVIDENCE APPEARATION FOR State of Kentucky County of Madison SS: I, Saml P. McMurtridy, Clerk of the County Court within and for the County and State aforesaid, do hereby certify that H. Y. Park Esq., before whom the foregoing affidavit, was made, and who has thereunto signed his name, was, at the time of so doing, a (2) Notary Public in and for the County and State above named, duly commissioned, qualified and sworn, that all of his official acts as such are entitled to full faith and credit, and that his said signature, as it appears on the reverse page hereof is genuine. Given under my hand and seal of Saml P. McMurtridy, Clerk of Office in Madison, this 4th day of September, 1844. R. P. McMurtridy, Clerk of Madison County Court By order of J. H. L. Edwards, Register. I certify that the foregoing signature has been carefully examined and the foregoing is genuine. In testimony whereof, I have hereunto set my hand and seal of office, this 4th day of September, 1844. S. P. McMurtridy Clerk 152744 105072 ACT OF JULY 14, 1862. Hoa. Chambers. Henderson Co. Ky. Widow of Aaron Chambers. Priv. Co. 118 U.S.C.T. Died at Va. Nov. 6th 1864. \"Dianhea\". Pension Office, 186. Respectfully referred to the Adjutant General, for official evidence of service and death. Joseph H. Barrett Commissioner. Received, Sept. 24th 1867. Claimant Henderson Ky. Attorney. No. 115.079 Kentucky Rose Chambers wid of Aaron Chambers Rank Pvt Company G Regiment 118, U.S.C. Troops Louisville Agency Rate for month $ 8 Commencing 7. Nov. 1864 Certificate dated 19. Dec. 1867 and sent to Claimant Henderson Ky Act 14th July, 1862 Book C Vol. 8 Page 21 Remain Clerk. SINGLE AFFIDAVIT FOR GENERAL PURPOSES IN UNITED STATES CLAIM EVIDENCE. A NEW RULE. The Department of the Interior, will not permit the Secretary of War to make any changes in the matter, unless the Secretary of War is authorized to make any changes in the matter, unless the Secretary of War is authorized to make any changes in the matter, unless the Secretary of War is authorized to make any changes in the matter. 18th St. JOHN HENRY JOHN'S OFFICE House to subscribed by ERNEST L. HART, ABON EITHER, Register of Pensions, No. State of Kentucky County of Indiana SS. On this 21st day of August A.D. 1867, before me H. S. Park, a Notary Public, I certify that the law of the State of Kentucky, is entitled to credit for the services rendered and paid by him, and that the pensioner is entitled to receive a pension of the 7th of July, 1866, being by me duly sworn according to law, on oath, that he is the true and lawful widow of Solomon Charles, decd. late a Private Company, Co. 111th U.S. Inf. Infantry, who died in field Hospital, State of Virginia, on the 21st day of November, 1866, from the affiant of Christian Anderson, for the time of duty. She further declares she is unable to obtain a certificate from the Surgeon of this Regiment or Company